<br>
The list has problems, that is that.  The point has been brought up that even if she didn't agree with all the rules of the list, Melissa WAS part of it and in the end did wrong by those rules (I'm sorry...  but I don't buy the little technicality defense...).  Frankly... I don't care so much if she broke the rules or not.  Forget about the stupid list.<br>
<br>
There is also the fact that she did not break any of the game rules as far as KSing and the like goes.  Yes, she got her epic piece fair and square.<br>
<br>
If she can live and be satisfied defending herself with the above two points, that is fine.  People view the game in different ways...some take it more serious than others.  <br>
<br>
That said, I think that the real issue for her should be one of what is morally right.  To show no respect for someone who has spent a HUGE chunk of their RL time waiting for that spawn can really make a huge statement about a person's character.  I understand that many people have given her a hard time and pulled her in many directions, and that can certainly influence her final decision... but it SHOULDN'T.   It should come down to the right, honest and decent thing to do... it should not be turned in out of spite and anger towards anyone who has been on Chami's side.  <br>
Again, I was not present at this incident, so I can only go by what has been said here... but from the situation as I understand it, I know that if I were in Melissa's shoes I absolutely could not live with myself if I took the epic piece for myself and ran.  She may have gotten the kill and looted it by breaking no technical rules, but she has broken a lot of trust, and now that she knows Chami's situation full and well, to still deny her of the epic piece that she sat and waited for so long would be just like spitting in her face in my honest opinion.  Either way, both clerics will eventually have their epics...whats really on the line is reputation.<br>
<br>
If its too late by now and Melissa has gotten her epic, I am very sorry Chami... at least you can know you have many people who were eager to defend you.  <br>
<br>
If it is not too late, I urge Melissa to think about kindness and respect for another human being's time rather than greed... even if many people HAVE been making nasty comments.<br>
<br>
Just my opinions here... not necessarily those of my guild.<br>
<br>
