<br>
I think the only person who seems to have been nice the whole way round on this is Chami and I don't even know her. I feel very sorry for her. I cannot imagine camping something for 2 weeks, let alone a month or more. You have my respect.<br>
<br>
But you were AFK. So was cleric #2.<br>
<br>
I used to think Melissa got her rage questionably. I am certainly no fan of the list, but if you sign it, essentially you say &quot;I agree with the list and will uphold it.&quot; She followed all of the procedures in place for LD/AFK clerics when Rage spawned and nothing happened. She got her friends to kill it with her.<br>
<br>
Grats Melisa. Hold your head high. You did nothing wrong. You have also done well in defending yourself. I would loathe to be in your situation.<br>
<br>
We can suggest changes all we want, but the fact is we have to deal with what we are dealt. Suggesting future changes to the quest (while many things can be done) does nothing for people who have to deal with the camp now.<br>
<br>
Ryee, your list (because it is yours, you enforce the rules) is flawed. Fix the flaws and maybe people will respect your list again someday.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Suggestions to fix the list</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
<br>
1) Require someone to send in screenshots of their Shimmering Pearl to the list and have them posted on a Pearl screenshots thread. Screenshots can be altered, yes, and anyone who does so I suppose will probably get away with it. Hard to prove something like this =/<br>
<br>
2) Minimum level 50 (yes, there are sub 50 clerics on the list). Note that provision 1 takes care of most level issues.<br>
<br>
3) People should not have to violate the EQ EULA to get their epic. Let people get some sleep for god's sake! Have people camp it in shifts of 8 hours. If Rage spawns during that person's designated 8 hours, great! They get rage! This means you are probably going to be in skyfire for a much longer time, however it also means you can have a *gasp* life! There can be many variations of this, just ease up on the camp requirement.<br>
<br>
Specifically for Ryee:<br>
4) Do not put your personal buddies in the list at arbitrary locations.<br>
<br>
5) Take a class in diplomacy. Your attitude does nothing to engender anyone to your cause.<br>
<br>
Not that my opinion matters... Of course nothing will ever be done until people realize that killing Rage outside &quot;The List&quot; is acceptable.<br>
<br>
